<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-14T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-14T13:00:00-05:00" n="261" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d261">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9338: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-14T14:00:00-04:00">August 14, 1937—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>216. Your 467, August 13, 3 p.m., and 473, August 13, 9 p.m. I heartily
                            approve the action taken by you.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
